<div class="markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark"><p data-start="0" data-end="144">Hereâ€™s a <strong data-start="9" data-end="26">short summary</strong> of how Functional Dependencies (FDs) cause issues at each normalization level and how they are <strong data-start="122" data-end="141">fixed using FDs</strong>:</p><hr data-start="146" data-end="149"><h3 data-start="151" data-end="182"><strong data-start="155" data-end="182">1NF (First Normal Form)</strong></h3><h4 data-start="183" data-end="200"><strong data-start="188" data-end="198">Issue:</strong></h4><ul data-start="201" data-end="357"><li data-start="201" data-end="273"><strong data-start="203" data-end="250">Repeating groups or multi-valued attributes</strong> (Non-atomic values).</li><li data-start="274" data-end="357"><strong data-start="276" data-end="297">FD Causing Issue:</strong> <code data-start="298" data-end="316">A â†’ {B1, B2, B3}</code> (Single column holds multiple values).</li></ul><h4 data-start="359" data-end="374">ong data-start="364" data-end="372">Fix:</strong></h4><ul data-start="375" data-end="520"><li data-start="375" data-end="444"><strong data-start="377" data-end="442">Convert multi-valued attributes into separate rows or tables.</strong></li><li data-start="445" data-end="520"><strong data-start="447" data-end="464">FD After Fix:</strong> <code data-start="465" data-end="472">A, B1</code> â†’ <code data-start="475" data-end="479">B2</code> (Each attribute holds a single value).</li></ul><hr data-start="522" data-end="525"><h3 data-start="527" data-end="559"><strong data-start="531" data-end="559">2NF (Second Normal Form)</strong></h3><h4 data-start="560" data-end="577"><strong data-start="565" data-end="575">Issue:</strong></h4><ul data-start="578" data-end="764"><li data-start="578" data-end="674"><strong data-start="580" data-end="603">Partial Dependency:</strong> A <strong data-start="606" data-end="627">non-key attribute</strong> depends on <strong data-start="639" data-end="671">only part of a composite k</strong>.</li><li data-start="675" data-end="764"><strong data-start="677" data-end="698">FD Causing Issue:</strong> <code data-start="699" data-end="711">{A, B} â†’ C</code>, but <code data-start="717" data-end="724">B â†’ C</code> (C depends only on part of <code data-start="752" data-end="760">{A, B}</code>).</li></ul><h4 data-start="766" data-end="781"><strong data-start="771" data-end="779">Fix:</strong></h4><ul data-start="782" data-end="900"><li data-start="782" data-end="839"><strong data-start="784" data-end="837">Move the dependent attribute to a separate table.</strong></li><li data-start="840" data-end="900"><strong data-start="842" data-end="859">FD After Fix:</strong> <code data-start="860" data-end="867">B â†’ C</code> (Separate table for <code data-start="888" data-end="896">{B, C}</code>).</li></ul><hr data-start="902" data-end="905"><h3 data-start="907" data-end="938"><strong data-start="911" data-end="938">3NF (Third Normal Form)</strong></h3><h4 data-start="939" data-end="956"><strong datt="944" data-end="954">Issue:</strong></h4><ul data-start="957" data-end="1149"><li data-start="957" data-end="1080"><strong data-start="959" data-end="985">Transitive Dependency:</strong> A <strong data-start="988" data-end="1009">non-key attribute</strong> depends on another <strong data-start="1029" data-end="1050">non-key attribute</strong> instead of the primary key.</li><li data-start="1081" data-end="1149"><strong data-start="1083" data-end="1104">FD Causing Issue:</strong> <code data-start="1105" data-end="1116">A â†’ B â†’ C</code> (C should depend on A, not B).</li></ul><h4 data-start="1151" data-end="1166"><strong data-start="1156" data-end="1164">Fix:</strong></h4><ul data-start="1167" data-end="1307"><li data-start="1167" data-end="1237"><strong data-start="1169" data-end="1235">Move the transitively dependent attribute to a separate table.</strong></li><li data-start="1238" data-end="1307"><strong data-start="1240" data-end="1257">FD After Fix:</strong> <code data-start="1258" data-end="1265">A /code> and <code data-start="1270" data-end="1277">B â†’ C</code> are now separate relations.</li></ul><hr data-start="1309" data-end="1312"><h3 data-start="1314" data-end="1351"><strong data-start="1318" data-end="1351">BCNF (Boyce-Codd Normal Form)</strong></h3><h4 data-start="1352" data-end="1369"><strong data-start="1357" data-end="1367">Issue:</strong></h4><ul data-start="1370" data-end="1540"><li data-start="1370" data-end="1462"><strong data-start="1372" data-end="1401">Candidate Key Dependency:</strong> A <strong data-start="1404" data-end="1459">non-superkey attribute determines another attribute</strong>.</li><li data-start="1463" data-end="1540"><strong data-start="1465" data-end="1486">FD Causing Issue:</strong> <code data-start="1487" data-end="1494">B â†’ A</code> (B is not a superkey, but it determines A).</li></ul><h4 data-start="1542" data-end="1557"><strong data-start="1547" data-end="1555">Fix:</strong></h4><ul data-start="1558" data-end="1680"><li data-start="1558" data-end="1604"><strong -start="1560" data-end="1602">Ensure all determinants are superkeys.</strong></li><li data-start="1605" data-end="1680"><strong data-start="1607" data-end="1624">FD After Fix:</strong> Make <code data-start="1630" data-end="1635">{B}</code> a new table or ensure <code data-start="1658" data-end="1663">{B}</code> is a superkey.</li></ul><hr data-start="1682" data-end="1685"><h3 data-start="1687" data-end="1719"><strong data-start="1691" data-end="1719">4NF (Fourth Normal Form)</strong></h3><h4 data-start="1720" data-end="1737"><strong data-start="1725" data-end="1735">Issue:</strong></h4><ul data-start="1738" data-end="1925"><li data-start="1738" data-end="1844"><strong data-start="1740" data-end="1774">Multi-Valued Dependency (MVD):</strong> One attribute can have <strong data-start="1798" data-end="1829">multiple independent values</strong> for another.</li><li data-start="1845" data-end="1925"><strong data-start="1847" data-end="1868">FD Causing Issue:</strong> <code data-start="1869" data-end="1877">A â†’â</code> and <code data-start="1882" data-end="1890">A â†’â†’ C</code> but <code data-start="1895" data-end="1898">B</code> and <code data-start="1903" data-end="1906">C</code> are independent.</li></ul><h4 data-start="1927" data-end="1942"><strong data-start="1932" data-end="1940">Fix:</strong></h4><ul data-start="1943" data-end="2051"><li data-start="1943" data-end="1986"><strong data-start="1945" data-end="1984">Decompose into two separate tables.</strong></li><li data-start="1987" data-end="2051"><strong data-start="1989" data-end="2006">FD After Fix:</strong> <code data-start="2007" data-end="2015">A â†’â†’ B</code> and <code data-start="2020" data-end="2028">A â†’â†’ C</code> in different tables.</li></ul><hr data-start="2053" data-end="2056"><h3 data-start="2058" data-end="2089"><strong data-start="2062" data-end="2089">5NF (Fifth Normal Form)</strong></h3><h4 data-start="2090" data-end="2107"><strong data-start="2095" data-end="2105">Issue:</strong></h4><ul data-start="2108" data-end="2315"><li data-stata-end="2224"><strong data-start="2110" data-end="2130">Join Dependency:</strong> A table can be split into <strong data-start="2157" data-end="2195">smaller tables without losing data</strong>, but isn't yet decomposed.</li><li data-start="2225" data-end="2315"><strong data-start="2227" data-end="2248">FD Causing Issue:</strong> <code data-start="2249" data-end="2260">{A, B, C}</code> should be split, but is kept together unnecessarily.</li></ul><h4 data-start="2317" data-end="2332"><strong data-start="2322" data-end="2330">Fix:</strong></h4><ul data-start="2333" data-end="2462"><li data-start="2333" data-end="2398"><strong data-start="2335" data-end="2396">Decompose into multiple tables to remove join dependency.</strong></li><li data-start="2399" data-end="2462"><strong data-start="2401" data-end="2418">FD After Fix:</strong> <code data-start="2419" data-end="2427">{A, B}</code> and <code data-start="2432" data-end="2440">{B, C}</code> in separate tables.</li></ul><hr data-start="2464" data-end="2467"><h3 data-start="2469" data-end="2490"><strong data-start="2473" data-end="2490">Final Summary</strong></h3><table data-start="2491" data-end="3188"><thead data-start="2491" data-end="2551"><tr data-start="2491" data-end="2551"><th data-start="2491" data-end="2501"><strong data-start="2493" data-end="2499">NF</strong></th><th data-start="2501" data-end="2526"><strong data-start="2503" data-end="2525">Issue Caused by FD</strong></th><th data-start="2526" data-end="2551"><strong data-start="2528" data-end="2549">Fix (New FD Form)</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="2609" data-end="3188"><tr data-start="2609" data-end="2692"><td><strong data-start="2611" data-end="2618">1NF</strong></td><td>Multi-valued attributes (Repeating groups).</td><td>Make attributes atomic.</td></tr><tr data-start="2693" data-end="2794"><td><strong data-start="2695" data-end="2702">2NF</strong></td><td>Partial dependency (Attribute depends on part of the key).</td><td>Remove partial dependency.</td></tr><tr data-start="2795" data-end="2894"><td><strong data-start="2797" data-end="2804">3NF</strong></td><td>Transitive dependency (Attribute depends on non-key).</td><td>Remove transitive dependency.</td></tr><tr data-start="2895" data-end="2977"><td><strong data-start="2897" data-end="2905">BCNF</strong></td><td>Non-superkey determinant.</td><td>Ensure every determinant is a superkey.</td></tr><tr data-start="2978" data-end="3090"><td><strong data-start="2980" data-end="2987">4NF</strong></td><td>Multi-valued dependency (Independent attributes in one table).</td><td>Remove multi-valued dependencies.</td></tr><tr data-start="3091" data-end="3188"><td><strong data-start="3093" data-end="3100">5NF</strong></td><td>Join dependency (Table can be split without data loss).</td><td>Remove join dependencies.</td></tr></tbody></table><p data-start="3190" data-end="3241" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Would you like specific table examples for each? ðŸ˜Š</p></div>